    "Second, we improved how user edits are processed to speed up proofreading.",
    "To make proofreading accessible, proofreaders should not need to be aware of the underlying data structures.",
    "Instead, users perform edits by placing line connectors for merges and points for splits (Fig. 2f).",
    "The ChunkedGraph implements splits with a maximum-flow minimum-cut operation where user-selected supervoxels are labeled as sources and sinks to find the edges in the graph that should be removed.",
    "Previously, many locations were needed to resolve complex false merges."
